1
00:00:05,770 --> 00:00:12,770
根据真实事件改编

2
00:00:14,240 --> 00:00:24,250
只有死者才能看到战争终结 ――柏拉图

3
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:58,350
1992年 东非 索马里

4
00:01:01,490 --> 00:01:07,160
多年来的部落战争 造成史无前例的饥荒

5
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:13,160
三十万人死于饥荒

6
00:01:16,410 --> 00:01:21,410
势力最强大的军阀艾迪德 掌控了首都摩加迪沙

7
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:30,880
他抢走国际组织运送的粮食 以饥荒作为他的武器

8
00:01:37,530 --> 00:01:40,460
他的恶行引起公愤

9
00:01:40,530 --> 00:01:46,200
两万名美国海军陆战队员被派到索马里 协助运送粮食并维持治安

10
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:56,480
1993年4月

11
00:01:56,550 --> 00:02:00,480
艾迪德等到美国海军陆战队一撤退

12
00:02:00,550 --> 00:02:05,210
便立刻向其余的联合国维和部队开战

13
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:16,960
在6月 艾迪德的民兵伏击和屠杀了24名巴基斯坦士兵

14
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:20,400
并开始攻击美国人

15
00:02:25,170 --> 00:02:27,110
8月底 美军派遣精锐部队

16
00:02:27,180 --> 00:02:30,170
三角洲部队 第75游骑兵团 以及第160特种作战航空团

17
00:02:30,210 --> 00:02:35,510
前往摩加迪沙推翻艾迪德 并重建秩序

18
00:02:39,090 --> 00:02:42,020
该任务原定为三个星期便结束

19
00:02:42,190 --> 00:02:47,190
但六个星期后 华盛顿失去耐性

20
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:59,680
黑  鹰  坠  落

21
00:03:01,110 --> 00:03:05,440
1993年10月2日 星期六

22
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:14,450
红十字会粮食分发中心

23
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:34,520
那里
There.

24
00:03:35,020 --> 00:03:36,790
九点钟方向有武装车
Technicals, nine o'clock.

25
00:04:02,290 --> 00:04:04,050
该死 你看到吗
Oh, shit! Did you see that?

26
00:04:04,450 --> 00:04:08,410
机长 在九点钟方向有平民遭到攻击
Chief, we got unarmed civilians getting shot down here at nine o'clock.

27
00:04:08,490 --> 00:04:11,260
看到了 但我们不能干涉
I got it, Matt. I don't think we can touch this.

28
00:04:14,390 --> 00:04:19,120
这些粮食是属于穆罕默德・法拉赫・艾迪德的 快滚回家吧

29
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,390
指挥官 这里是超级64号
Command, Super 64...

30
00:04:21,470 --> 00:04:25,270
民兵在粮食分发中心扫射平民
we got militia shooting unarmed civilians down at the food distribution center.

31
00:04:25,340 --> 00:04:26,970
请求准许攻击
Request permission to engage.

32
00:04:27,210 --> 00:04:29,770
超级64号 你有受到攻击吗
Super 64, are you taking fire? Over.

33
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:31,710
没有 指挥官
Negative, command.

34
00:04:31,850 --> 00:04:34,870
那里属于联合国管辖 我们不能干涉
U.N. 's jurisdiction, 64. We cannot intervene.

35
00:04:34,950 --> 00:04:37,010
- 返回基地 - 收到
- Return to base. Over. - Roger.

36
00:04:37,790 --> 00:04:39,250
64号返回基地
64 returning.

37
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:52,310
摩加迪沙 巴卡拉市集 艾迪德势力范围

38
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,020
可以走了 奥图先生

39
00:05:40,380 --> 00:05:41,410
他要走了
Leaving.

40
00:06:07,130 --> 00:06:08,390
先生

41
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,730
继续开

42
00:06:24,410 --> 00:06:26,400
我恐怕要迟到

43
00:06:26,450 --> 00:06:28,420
待会儿再打给你

44
00:06:46,580 --> 00:06:48,310
加里森将军
General Garrison?

45
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:49,940
谢了 我有了
No, no, thanks. I got one.

46
00:06:50,020 --> 00:06:51,350
这是古巴雪茄
But these are Cuban.

47
00:06:52,050 --> 00:06:53,950
上好的保利瓦雪茄
Bolivar Belicoso.

48
00:06:54,460 --> 00:06:55,620
这也是
So is this.

49
00:06:57,890 --> 00:06:59,950
那是迈阿密产的 我的朋友 这没古巴的好
Miami, my friend, is not Cuba.

50
00:07:07,670 --> 00:07:10,640
你们老是抓不到艾迪德
I see not catching Aidid is becoming a routine.

51
00:07:11,570 --> 00:07:14,010
这次我们要抓的不是艾迪德 我们要抓的是你
We weren't trying to catch Aidid. We were trying to catch you.

52
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,100
我
Me?

53
00:07:15,710 --> 00:07:17,440
我有这么重要吗
But am I that important?

54
00:07:18,110 --> 00:07:19,710
我想破头也想不出我有多重要
I hardly think so.

55
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:22,980
- 你是个生意人 - 只是混口饭吃而已
- You're just a businessman. - Trying to make a living.

56
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:25,850
对 而且你贩卖枪枝给艾迪德的民兵
Yeah. Selling guns to Aidid's militia.

57
00:07:30,890 --> 00:07:32,520
你来了多久
You've been here, what?

58
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:35,520
六个星期
Six weeks?

59
00:07:37,630 --> 00:07:40,760
六星期来你一直想抓到他
Six weeks you are trying to catch the general.

60
00:07:41,270 --> 00:07:43,470
到处张帖悬赏海报
You put up reward posters.

61
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:48,310
两万五千美元 这算什么 你想演《终结追杀令》吗
$25,000. What is this? Gunfight at the K.O. Corral?

62
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:51,950
是《绝命追杀令》
It's the O.K. Corral.

63
00:07:52,980 --> 00:07:56,820
你以为把我抓来他就会自首
Do you think bringing me in will make him suddenly come to you?

64
00:07:57,350 --> 00:07:59,120
乖乖束手就擒
Make him more agreeable?

65
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,960
你知道他在哪里
You know where he sleeps.

66
00:08:04,730 --> 00:08:07,700
你资助他的一切 包括民兵
You pay for his beds, much less his militia.

67
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,590
我们逮不到他就不会离开索马里
We're not leaving Somalia till we find him.

68
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:15,860
我们一定会逮到他
And we will find him.

69
00:08:15,940 --> 00:08:18,980
别以为我不是喝自来水长大的…
Don't make the mistake of thinking because I grew up without running water...

70
00:08:19,010 --> 00:08:20,640
就认为我是个笨蛋
I am simple, General.

71
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:24,010
我对历史很了解
I do know something about history.

72
00:08:24,850 --> 00:08:28,440
你看到吗 我们在创造明天
See all this? It's simply shaping tomorrow.

73
00:08:29,410 --> 00:08:33,470
指克林顿总统

74
00:08:29,890 --> 00:08:33,980
一个没有阿肯色州白小子干涉我们内政的明天
A tomorrow without a lot of Arkansas white boys' ideas in it.

75
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:37,320
这点我倒不清楚 我是德州人
Well, I wouldn't know about that. I'm from Texas.

76
00:08:37,460 --> 00:08:41,590
加里森将军 你们不该来这儿
Mr. Garrison, I think you shouldn't have come here.

77
00:08:42,270 --> 00:08:43,790
这是内战
This is civil war.

78
00:08:45,130 --> 00:08:46,600
这是我们的战争
This is our war.

79
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:48,970
不是你们的
Not yours.

80
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,600
三十万人死亡
300,000 dead and counting.

81
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:57,180
这不是战争 奥图先生 这是种族屠杀
That's not a war, Mr. Atto. That's genocide.

82
00:08:58,550 --> 00:09:00,950
喝茶吧
Now, you enjoy that tea, you hear?

83
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:08,690
你觉得他怎样
How'd he strike you?

84
00:09:08,930 --> 00:09:11,950
彬彬有礼 冷酷无情
Urbane, sophisticated, cruel.

85
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:13,790
他是一条大鱼
Yeah, he's a good catch.

86
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:16,650
时间一久 艾迪德就会感到受制了
It'll take time, but Aidid will feel the loss.

87
00:09:16,730 --> 00:09:19,390
我们没有太多时间
I'm not sure time is something we got in great supply.

88
00:09:19,470 --> 00:09:23,170
这里比伊拉克的情形要复杂
This isn't lraq, you know. Much more complicated than that.

89
00:09:24,140 --> 00:09:26,040
但华盛顿官员可不这么想
Boss, most of Washington might disagree.

90
00:09:26,110 --> 00:09:29,170
这个星期他们每天早上都打电话来
I'm just saying they've been calling for these dang situation reports...

91
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:30,970
要那该死的形势报告
every morning this week.

92
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:35,750
你就告诉他们说战争一触即发
Well, tell them the situation is fragile.

93
00:09:38,610 --> 00:09:42,100
摩加迪沙机场 美国陆军指挥总部

94
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:45,090
女士们 先生们 先大家好 我是克里夫・"猫王"・渥尔考特
Ladies and gentlemen, my name is Cliff "Elvis" Wolcott.

95
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:46,790
本次航班的机长
I'll be your pilot this afternoon.

96
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:50,960
这架黑鹰直升机是非吸烟区
Federal regulations has designated the non-smoking Black Hawk helicopter.

97
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:53,700
凡经常飞摩加迪沙的本公司会员
For those of you moved on Mogadishu frequent flyer program...

98
00:09:53,770 --> 00:09:55,790
可以累积100点的哩程优惠
you'll be earning 100 free credits this afternoon.

99
00:09:55,870 --> 00:10:00,400
呕吐袋就放在前座的椅背
And as always, the air sickness bags are located in the seatback in front of you.

100
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:04,100
1号发动机正常 克里夫 检查2号发动机
Number one indications are good, Cliff. Put her on two.

101
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:05,650
没问题
You're still clear.

102
00:10:20,730 --> 00:10:24,190
61号 这里是64号 使用超高频无线电
61, this is 64. Go to UHF secure.

103
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:25,890
我有个坏消息
I've got some bad news.

104
00:10:26,290 --> 00:10:29,050
Limo为豪华轿车

105
00:10:26,740 --> 00:10:29,530
"Limo"是一个词 杜兰特 别再跟我罗唆
"Limo" is a word, Durant. I don't want to hear about it.

106
00:10:29,610 --> 00:10:32,540
那是缩写 不是一个词
It is not a word. It's an abbreviation of a word.

107
00:10:32,610 --> 00:10:34,600
"Limo"是常用语
"Limo" is a word in common usage.

108
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:38,670
拼字游戏的规则是接受常用语 我的好朋友
That is the key phrase in Scrabble, my good friend. Common usage.

109
00:10:38,750 --> 00:10:41,580
不 字典查不到就不算
No, if it's not in the dictionary it doesn't count!

110
00:10:41,650 --> 00:10:43,850
字典查不到也算
It doesn't have to be in the dictionary!

111
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:46,080
字典查不到就不算
It does have to be in the dictionary!

112
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:49,720
听着 等我回基地我就把这个词给剔除掉
Listen, when we get back to the base, it's coming off the board.

113
00:10:49,780 --> 00:10:53,040
此处Limo指男性器官

114
00:10:50,290 --> 00:10:53,560
你敢碰我的"Limo" 我就揍你 懂吗
You touch my "limo" and I'll spank you, Nightstalker. You hear me?

115
00:10:53,630 --> 00:10:55,190
你有种揍我才怪呢
Yeah, promises.

116
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:57,870
好美的海滩
That's a nice beach down there.

117
00:10:58,370 --> 00:10:59,700
海水怎样
How's the water?

118
00:10:59,940 --> 00:11:03,670
很暖和 到处都是鲨鱼
Yeah, it's nice and warm. And it's loaded with sharks.

119
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:16,010
这敢情好
That's great.

120
00:11:16,090 --> 00:11:18,850
- 你觉得这很好玩吗 - 不
- Thinks he's funny. - Yeah. Well, I don't.

121
00:11:22,090 --> 00:11:23,180
听到吗
Hear that?

122
00:11:23,260 --> 00:11:25,390
- 紧张吗 - 我严阵以待
- Nervous? - I'm ready to go, man.

123
00:11:31,070 --> 00:11:32,970
多么适合作战的一天
Beautiful day to fight.

124
00:11:36,110 --> 00:11:37,900
- 名字 - 托迪
- Name. - Todd.

125
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:39,740
- 姓 - 布莱克博德
- Last name. - Blackburn.

126
00:11:41,410 --> 00:11:43,110
名字是托迪
First name, Todd.

127
00:11:43,550 --> 00:11:46,280
- 这里怎样 - 什么怎样
- So, what's it like? - What's what like?

128
00:11:46,350 --> 00:11:47,750
摩加迪沙 有仗打吗
Mogadishu. The fighting.

129
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:51,380
- 士兵证号码 - 72163427
- Serial number. - 72163427.

130
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:56,600
把Mogadishu砍掉一半读成Mog后 就和停尸房Morgue的读音相近了

131
00:11:53,020 --> 00:11:56,690
首先 大家都会说"莫格" 而不会说"摩加迪沙"
Firstly, it's "the Mog" or simply "Mog." No one calls it Mogadishu here.

132
00:11:56,760 --> 00:12:00,060
其次 就是有仗打也没我的份 所以别问我
Secondly, I wouldn't know about the fighting, so don't ask.

133
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:01,760
为什么
Why not?

134
00:12:02,260 --> 00:12:04,230
我叫你别问了
Didn't I just say, "Don't ask"?

135
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:09,360
你不是游骑兵
You're not a Ranger.

136
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:11,670
我当了6年的游骑兵
I am a Ranger. Six years.

137
00:12:11,870 --> 00:12:14,810
我在巴拿马追捕过诺列加 还参加过海湾战争
I was in Panama chasing down Noriega, and in the Gulf.

138
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,370
我可是个老兵 伙计
I'm a vet, my friend.

139
00:12:16,450 --> 00:12:17,640
参加过战斗
In combat?

140
00:12:18,780 --> 00:12:22,340
你真像个12岁小孩子 我来解释一下：
Look, kid, you look like you're about 12, so let me explain something to you.

141
00:12:22,420 --> 00:12:26,720
我有一种特殊的才能 不必参与战斗
I have a rare and mysterious skill that precludes me from going into missions.

142
00:12:27,390 --> 00:12:28,410
打字
Typing.

143
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:30,590
- 你会打字吗 - 不会
- Can you type? - No.

144
00:12:32,290 --> 00:12:35,290
- 生日 - 1975年2月27日
- Date of birth. - 2-27-75.

145
00:12:41,370 --> 00:12:43,130
我是来踢爆坏人的卵蛋的
Well, I'm here to kick some ass.

146
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,200
回去吧
Let's bring it in.

147
00:13:05,190 --> 00:13:06,960
干得漂亮 伙计
Nice, man! Very smooth!

148
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:09,390
一枪就打穿发动机了
Single shot through the engine block.

149
00:13:09,900 --> 00:13:12,490
真可惜 那辆吉普车挺帅的
Shit, that's a shame. That was a nice jeep.

150
00:13:38,260 --> 00:13:40,160
停止射击 停止射击
Cease fire! Cease fire!

151
00:13:40,630 --> 00:13:41,740
检查武器

152
00:13:47,570 --> 00:13:49,000
草泥马的"三角洲"
Fucking Delta.

153
00:13:49,770 --> 00:13:51,030
埃利斯曼中士
Sergeant Eversmann.

154
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:54,910
- 中士 - 什么事
- Sergeant. - Yeah?

155
00:13:54,980 --> 00:13:56,880
我是一等兵布莱克博德
Private First Class Blackburn.

156
00:13:57,010 --> 00:13:58,100
什么事
Yeah?

157
00:13:58,380 --> 00:13:59,870
我来报到
Reporting for duty.

158
00:14:00,050 --> 00:14:02,130
你应该向比尔斯中尉报到
Not to me you're not. You're reporting to Lt. Beales.

159
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:04,380
他应该就在附近
He should be around here somewhere.

160
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:06,250
我把他交给你了
Can I leave him with you?

161
00:14:06,790 --> 00:14:08,190
好吧
Yeah, go ahead.

162
00:14:09,230 --> 00:14:11,280
- 你带武器了吗 - 带了 长官
- You brought your weapon. - Yes, sir.

163
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,260
我不累 我能练靶吗
Want me to shoot? I'm rested.

164
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:16,500
- 什么时候到的 - 刚到
- When did you get in? - Just now, Sarg'nt.

165
00:14:16,770 --> 00:14:18,320
先做重要的事
First things first.

166
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:22,570
这会是你在非洲最好的朋友
This will be your best friend in all of Africa.

167
00:14:22,770 --> 00:14:24,330
它叫"牛蛙"
It's called BullFrog.

168
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:26,840
抹一点到脸上
Get some on over here, all right?

169
00:14:26,910 --> 00:14:28,210
是的 长官
Yes, sir.

170
00:14:28,740 --> 00:14:31,240
嘿 施密德 帮我带一下队
Hey, Schmid! Take over for me, would you?

171
00:14:33,580 --> 00:14:35,780
好了 先去把东西放好
All right. Let's get you unpacked.

172
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:42,890
谁饿了
Hey, who's hungry?

173
00:15:04,980 --> 00:15:08,470
这算什么 纳税人出钱组织的三角洲野餐队吗
What is this, Sarg'nt? Another taxpayer-funded Delta safari?

174
00:15:08,050 --> 00:15:14,050
Jeff Sanderson为电影中化名 这位三级军士长真名叫Paul Howe 退役后开了自己的战术培训学校

175
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:11,310
- 如果加里森将军问起可别说 - 我问起呢
- Not if General Garrison is asking. - I'm asking.

176
00:15:12,450 --> 00:15:14,180
用餐愉快 上尉
Have a nice meal, Captain.

177
00:15:18,930 --> 00:15:21,190
- 嘿 伙计 大家都在排队 - 我知道
- Hey, man, there's a line. - I know.

178
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:24,430
- 你这是插队 - 我也知道
- Well, this isn't the back of it. - Yeah, I know.

179
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:28,500
军士 军士
Sergeant. Sergeant.

180
00:15:29,270 --> 00:15:30,470
这是怎么回事
What's going on here?

181
00:15:30,540 --> 00:15:33,510
我们练靶的时候打到了一只野猪
Some aerial target practice, sir. Didn't want to leave it behind.

182
00:15:33,580 --> 00:15:35,510
我是说你的武器
I'm talking about your weapon.

183
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:37,760
hot weapon指武器上了膛同时又打开了保险

184
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:38,240
三角洲也不能拿一把开着保险的枪到处乱晃
Now, Delta or no Delta, that's a hot weapon.

185
00:15:38,610 --> 00:15:41,980
你应该很清楚 在基地里 任何时候枪都要关着保险
You know better than that. Safety should be on at all times on base.

186
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:46,000
这一段是编导在瞎掰 现实中D-BOYS都是非常注意保险的
比如Sanderson的原型Paul Howe在他的经验里都十分强调保险的作用

187
00:15:42,050 --> 00:15:44,020
这就是我的"保险"
Well, this is my safety, sir.

188
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:50,180
别管他 他好几天没吃饭了
Let it go, sir. The guy hasn't eaten in a couple of days.

189
00:15:50,260 --> 00:15:53,420
你那帮三角小崽子只是一群目无纪律的牛仔
You Delta boys are a bunch of undisciplined cowboys.

190
00:15:53,860 --> 00:15:55,690
我告诉你
Let me tell you something, Sarg'nt.

191
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:59,530
到了前线 你会需要游骑兵的支援的
When we get on the five-yard line, you're going to need my Rangers.

192
00:15:59,770 --> 00:16:02,260
你们最好学学什么是团队精神
So y'all better learn to be team players.

193
00:16:03,470 --> 00:16:04,840
我说完了
We're done here.

194
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:17,810
说呀 你说这是保险
Speak up. You say this is your safety?

195
00:16:18,250 --> 00:16:20,080
这是我的靴子
Well, this is my boot, son.

196
00:16:21,090 --> 00:16:24,460
小心我用这只靴子把你踢爆
And it will fit up your asses with the proper amount of force.

197
00:16:24,530 --> 00:16:28,090
- 这是新泽西口音吗 - 拜托 我很努力耶
- Is that a Jersey accent? - I'm trying to do this, give me a break.

198
00:16:28,530 --> 00:16:30,360
把太阳眼镜脱掉
Take those sunglasses off, soldier.

199
00:16:30,430 --> 00:16:32,870
"三角洲"喜欢戴Ｏ记眼镜 那是他们的事
Delta wants to wear Oakleys, that's their business.

200
00:16:32,940 --> 00:16:35,630
别让我再看到你戴
I don't want to see them on you again. Hoo-ah?

201
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:38,430
这把枪上了膛
Is that a hot weapon?

202
00:16:43,980 --> 00:16:45,340
你下了吗
Is that your move?

203
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:47,380
手还没离棋啊
Is my hand on the piece?

204
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:49,840
再下三步我就赢了
I can mate you in three whatever you do.

205
00:16:51,590 --> 00:16:55,180
你自己小心点吧 我正盯着你的"女王"呢
I'd keep my eye on that queen before counseling with the others.

206
00:16:55,590 --> 00:16:57,560
她躺在那儿等着呢
Well, she's just lying in wait.

207
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:03,100
进退维谷吧 戈登
Stranded and condemned, Gordy.

208
00:17:03,270 --> 00:17:04,320
该你了
Your move.

209
00:17:05,670 --> 00:17:06,670
克里布斯
Cribbs.

210
00:17:06,740 --> 00:17:07,740
伊格斯
Yikes.

211
00:17:09,970 --> 00:17:12,570
你画得越来越好了
It's good. You're really improving.

212
00:17:13,410 --> 00:17:16,240
不过我有一个建议
If I may make a suggestion... Observation.

213
00:17:16,310 --> 00:17:17,400
说吧
Go ahead.

214
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:19,810
- 这是童话故事 对吧 - 没错
- It's a children's book, right? - Right.

215
00:17:20,450 --> 00:17:24,580
这会把小孩子吓得屁滚尿流
They are not supposed to scare the living shit out of the children.

216
00:17:24,650 --> 00:17:27,000
这里说到我们的的骑士…
This is the part of the story where our knight, our warrior...

217
00:17:27,020 --> 00:17:28,500
正要屠掉独眼巨龙
is about to slay the one-eyed dragon.

218
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:31,220
本来就很可怕 而且我女儿最喜欢了
That's scary. Besides, my daughter loves this stuff.

219
00:17:31,290 --> 00:17:33,490
我以为你上礼拜就画完了
Thought you finished that last week.

220
00:17:33,930 --> 00:17:35,190
你说完了吗
You done?

221
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:40,330
就快冲到十码线了
Hey, we are at the 10-yard line here, men.

222
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,890
明白吗
You understand?

223
00:17:41,890 --> 00:17:44,550
讥讽美式足球运动员的智商

224
00:17:42,270 --> 00:17:44,970
你会数数吗 一 二 十
Can you count? One, two, ten.

225
00:17:44,790 --> 00:17:46,950
美式足球里持球跑动进攻的球员

226
00:17:45,270 --> 00:17:47,440
我的跑卫呢
Okay? Where are my running backs?

227
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:49,410
我的跑卫哪去了
Where are my running backs?

228
00:17:50,950 --> 00:17:54,070
我没看到你做礼拜
Hey, I didn't see you at church on Sunday, soldier.

229
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:56,340
你有别的事吗
You had something more important to do?

230
00:17:56,420 --> 00:17:58,910
礼拜天一定要做礼拜
Not on Sunday, you don't. Not anymore.

231
00:17:58,990 --> 00:18:01,390
别给我落跑 了解吗
I will make you believe, you understand?

232
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:18,000
很好笑
Pretty funny, hoo-ah?

233
00:18:20,910 --> 00:18:23,940
你学得很像 很像我
It was a good impression. I recognize myself.

234
00:18:27,050 --> 00:18:28,520
你们继续吧
All right, carry on.

235
00:18:29,590 --> 00:18:32,420
- 我要跟你讲话 - 是 长官
- I'd like a word, specialist. - Sir.

236
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:36,410
你知道谁有指挥权吧
Tell me, Pilla, you understand why we have a chain of command, don't you?

237
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:37,650
知道 长官
Roger that, sir.

238
00:18:37,730 --> 00:18:39,530
你敢再取笑我…
'Cause if I ever see you undermine me again...

239
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:41,440
我就要你把马桶舔干净
you'll be cleaning latrines with your tongue...

240
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:44,100
保证你一个月吃不下饭
till you can't taste the difference between shit and French fries.

241
00:18:44,170 --> 00:18:45,530
- 明白吗 - 明白了
- Are we clear? - Hoo-ah, sir.

242
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:46,600
好了
All right.

243
00:18:54,340 --> 00:18:55,640
听好
Listen to this:

244
00:18:55,710 --> 00:19:00,480
当一个索马里人杀了人 他的部落就欠对方部落一百只骆驼
If one skinny kills another skinny, his clan owes the dead guy's clan a hundred camels.

245
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,010
一百只骆驼
A hundred camels.

246
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:04,610
我连一只都不给
Camels. I wouldn't pay one camel.

247
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:06,950
这儿的人一定都欠了一屁股的骆驼债
Must be a lot of fucking camel debt.

248
00:19:07,490 --> 00:19:09,480
这是真的吗
Is that really true, Lieutenant?

249
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:11,960
去问埃利斯曼中士 他喜欢非洲人
Ask Sgt. Eversmann. He likes the skinnies.

250
00:19:12,030 --> 00:19:14,660
埃利斯曼中士 那是真的吗?
Sgt. Eversmann, you really like the skinnies?

251
00:19:15,260 --> 00:19:19,200
不是喜欢不喜欢的问题 我尊重他们
It's not that I like them or I don't like them. I respect them.

252
00:19:19,270 --> 00:19:23,730
你们意识到埃利斯曼中士是个理想主义者了吧
See, what you guys fail to realize is the sergeant is a bit of an idealist.

253
00:19:23,810 --> 00:19:27,370
他相信这项任务的使命对吧 中士
He believes in this mission down to his very bones. Don't you, Sergeant?

254
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:30,710
这些人没有工作
Look, these people, they have no jobs...

255
00:19:31,110 --> 00:19:35,070
没有食物 教育和未来
no food, no education, no future.

256
00:19:35,150 --> 00:19:38,710
我只是觉得我们有两个选择
I just figure that, I mean, we have two things that we can do.

257
00:19:38,790 --> 00:19:40,080
帮助他们
We can either help...

258
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:43,590
或是眼睁睁看着他们自相残杀
or we can sit back and watch the country destroy itself on CNN.

259
00:19:43,890 --> 00:19:44,890
对吧
Right?

260
00:19:45,390 --> 00:19:48,490
我不知道 我是来打仗的
I don't know about you guys, but I was trained to fight.

261
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:50,460
你不是吗
Are you trained to fight, Sergeant?

262
00:19:50,530 --> 00:19:53,660
我是来改善世界的
Well, I think I was trained to make a difference, Kurth.

263
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:56,990
他真的很有理想
Like the man said, he's an idealist.

264
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,770
等等 我最爱这一段
Oh, wait. This is my favorite part.

265
00:20:06,250 --> 00:20:08,110
滚远一点
Stay away from the cans!

266
00:20:08,350 --> 00:20:10,380
去死吧 猪头
Die, gas-pumper!

267
00:20:11,390 --> 00:20:13,180
给我滚远一点
Stay away from those cans!

268
00:20:15,220 --> 00:20:16,420
比尔斯
Beales!

269
00:20:18,090 --> 00:20:20,080
不 退后
No, no, stay back, stay back.

270
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:23,150
他的癫痫症发作了 拿东西让他咬着
He's having a seizure. Put something in his mouth.

271
00:20:23,370 --> 00:20:27,960
约翰 没事了…没事了
John, it's okay. John, it's okay. It's okay.

272
00:20:29,260 --> 00:20:37,220
10月3日 星期天 清晨5:45

273
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:17,850
他没事了 不过他得退伍
Well, he'll be fine. But not in this army.

274
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:21,320
他有癫痫症 我得送他回家
He's out of the game. He's epileptic, going home.

275
00:21:25,380 --> 00:21:29,380
按照马克・鲍顿原著里的解释 Chalk为游骑兵的一个12人战斗小分队
但根据美国陆军作战条令 Chalk为"黑鹰"在空中突击中运载的一个11人小分队

276
00:21:25,690 --> 00:21:28,030
我要你来带领他的小分队
I'm putting you in charge of his chalk.

277
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:31,600
- 有什么问题吗 - 没有 长官
- You got a problem with that? - No, sir.

278
00:21:31,670 --> 00:21:33,760
这个责任很重大
Now, it's a big responsibility.

279
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:36,110
你的弟兄们依赖你
Your men are gonna look to you to make the right decisions.

280
00:21:36,140 --> 00:21:37,830
他们的命都在你手上
Their lives depend on it.

281
00:21:39,340 --> 00:21:40,570
好了
All right.

282
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:43,500
"Rangers, lead the way" 乃游骑兵口号

283
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:44,010
- 游骑兵 做先锋 - 勇往直前
- Rangers lead the way, sir. - All the way.

284
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:46,170
祝好运
Good luck, Sergeant.

285
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:53,300
巴卡拉市集 哈瓦迪街 艾迪德民兵的据点

286
00:22:29,660 --> 00:22:34,430
艾迪德势力的高级成员今天下午三点可能要开会
A long anticipated meeting of Aidid's senior cabinet may take place today at 1500 hours.

287
00:22:35,260 --> 00:22:38,230
我说"可能"是因为…
I say "may" because we all know by now...

288
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:41,390
根据目前的情报 一切都不确定
with the intel we get on the street, nothing is certain.

289
00:22:41,670 --> 00:22:44,500
这是三方确定的情报
This is actual intel confirmed by three sources.

290
00:22:45,510 --> 00:22:48,570
两名高层成员可能会在场
Two tier-one personalities may be present:

291
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:52,780
艾迪德的政治顾问奥玛・萨拉德
Omar Salad, Aidid's top political advisor...

292
00:22:52,850 --> 00:22:55,440
内政部长阿迪・哈桑・阿瓦利
and Abdi Hassan Awale, lnterior Minister.

293
00:22:55,550 --> 00:22:57,540
他们是我们的目标
These are the guys we're after.

294
00:22:58,420 --> 00:22:59,790
今天就行动
Today we go.

295
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:02,350
任务计划和以前一样
Same mission template as before.

296
00:23:03,190 --> 00:23:07,290
15:45时 三角洲的突击小组攻入敌方建筑物
1545, Assault Force Delta will infiltrate the target building...

297
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:09,590
逮捕里面所有的嫌疑人
and seize all suspects within.

298
00:23:09,730 --> 00:23:14,030
警戒部队为游骑兵的四个小分队 由斯蒂尔上尉指挥
Security Force Rangers: 4 Ranger chalks, under the command of Captain Steele...

299
00:23:14,100 --> 00:23:16,200
在15:46时滑降到地面
will rope in at 1546...

300
00:23:16,270 --> 00:23:19,640
在目标建筑外围的四个角建立防线
and hold a four-corner perimeter around the target building.

301
00:23:20,110 --> 00:23:21,630
任何人不得进出
No one gets in or out.

302
00:23:21,710 --> 00:23:23,230
撤退部队
Extraction Force:

303
00:23:23,650 --> 00:23:28,450
麦肯奈特中校的悍马车队在15:47时开进哈瓦迪街
Lt. Colonel McKnight's humvee column will drive into the city at 1547...

304
00:23:28,520 --> 00:23:32,350
停在奥林匹克旅馆前
on Hawlwadig Road and hold just short of the Olympic Hotel here.

305
00:23:32,420 --> 00:23:34,010
等待指示
Wait for the green light.

306
00:23:34,090 --> 00:23:36,110
当三角洲部队突击成功
Now once Delta gives the word...

307
00:23:36,190 --> 00:23:38,720
麦肯奈特的手下前往目标建筑
McKnight's column will move to the target building...

308
00:23:38,790 --> 00:23:41,230
把犯人架上车
and load the prisoners on flatbed trucks.

309
00:23:41,630 --> 00:23:44,000
把犯人架上车后
Immediately after the prisoners are loaded...

310
00:23:44,070 --> 00:23:48,160
游骑兵的四个小分队立即到目标大楼集合
the four Ranger chalks will collapse back to the target building...

311
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:50,030
一起上悍马车队
load up on humvees...

312
00:23:50,110 --> 00:23:53,970
然后地面部队就一路返回基地
and the entire ground force will exfil the 3 miles back to base.

313
00:23:54,040 --> 00:23:57,810
行动时间预计不足30分钟
Mission time from incursion to extraction, no longer than 30 minutes.

314
00:23:58,650 --> 00:24:03,520
我原本请求调动装甲车辆和AC-130"幽灵"炮艇机支援
Now, I had requested light armor and AC-130 Spectre gunships...

315
00:24:03,590 --> 00:24:07,250
但华盛顿却不同意
but Washington, in all its wisdom, decided against this.

316
00:24:07,960 --> 00:24:09,750
他们认为太高调了
Too high-profile.

317
00:24:09,830 --> 00:24:13,090
所以行动将由"黑鹰"和"小鸟"
So Black Hawks and Little Birds will provide the air cover...

318
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:15,360
用Minigun和2.75英寸火箭提供空中支援
with miniguns and 2.75 rockets.

319
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:16,930
哈勒尔上校
Colonel Harrell.

320
00:24:16,990 --> 00:24:21,450
C-2即"指挥"Commando和"控制"Control

321
00:24:17,430 --> 00:24:21,890
在C-2直升机上 马修斯上校负责空中支援的调度
In the C-2 bird, Colonel Matthews will coordinate the air mission...

322
00:24:22,170 --> 00:24:25,000
而我负责指挥地面部队
and I will coordinate ground forces.

323
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:26,540
马修斯上校
Colonel Matthews.

324
00:24:26,610 --> 00:24:29,910
本次任务的代号为"艾琳"
Mission launch code word is lrene.

325
00:24:30,550 --> 00:24:31,640
有问题吗
Questions?

326
00:24:34,620 --> 00:24:36,350
目标是哪栋建筑
Which building is it, sir?

327
00:24:36,420 --> 00:24:38,420
目前还不清楚准确的目标建筑
Exactly which building, we're confirming right now.

328
00:24:38,490 --> 00:24:40,820
只知道是巴卡拉市集附近
Somewhere around the Bakara Market.

329
00:24:42,720 --> 00:24:45,720
我不能替他们决定开会的时间地点
I don't choose the time or place of their meetings.

330
00:24:45,890 --> 00:24:47,690
我不是这个意思
I didn't say a word, sir.

331
00:24:48,100 --> 00:24:51,530
大家听好 你们到了巴卡拉市集
Make no mistake, once you're in the Bakara Market...

332
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:54,000
就等于进入战区
you're in an entirely hostile district.

333
00:24:54,570 --> 00:24:57,090
千万别低估敌人实力
Don't underestimate their capabilities.

334
00:24:57,170 --> 00:25:00,840
进入市集之前都不是战区
Now we'll be going through friendly neighborhoods before we hit the market...

335
00:25:00,910 --> 00:25:05,110
千万切记交战规则 遭到攻击后才能还击
so remember the rules of engagement: No one fires unless fired upon.

336
00:25:05,610 --> 00:25:07,880
完成这件任务吧
Now, let's go get this thing done.

337
00:25:08,980 --> 00:25:10,610
祝大家好运
Good luck, gentlemen.

338
00:25:15,560 --> 00:25:18,490
还有什么不满吗 丹尼
What's the matter, Danny? Something you don't like?

339
00:25:18,690 --> 00:25:21,060
没有"幽灵"炮艇机 而且是白天的行动…
No Spectre gunships, daylight instead of night...

340
00:25:21,130 --> 00:25:23,830
那些索马里佬在下午特别精神
late afternoon when they're all fucked up on khat...

341
00:25:23,900 --> 00:25:28,430
而那里又是艾迪德的根据地 火力集中
only part of the city Aidid can mount a serious counter-attack on short notice...

342
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:31,130
- 我还能什么不满的 - 人生不如意事十常八九
